   "source": [
    "Descriptive Statistics: Descriptive statistics involve summarizing and describing data to provide a clear and concise understanding of its main features. It includes measures like mean, median, mode, range, variance, and standard deviation. Descriptive statistics are used to organize, present, and analyze data to reveal patterns and trends.\n",
    "\n",
    "Example: Calculating the average income (mean) of a group of individuals.\n",
    "\n",
    "Inferential Statistics: Inferential statistics go beyond describing data and involve making predictions, inferences, or conclusions about a population based on a sample of data. It uses techniques like hypothesis testing, confidence intervals, and regression analysis to draw inferences about the entire population from which the sample was drawn.\n",
    "\n",
    "Example: Conducting a hypothesis test to determine if a new marketing strategy has a significant impact on sales based on a sample of customer data."
   ]
